        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I leave you with the words of the mystic St. Teresa of Avila. “Christ has no body now but yours, no hands but yours.” Whatever your beliefs, the point is clear. Whatever good we want done, we’ll have to do it ourselves. And there will be reasons not to do this good. Your midterm. Your paper. Your application. It doesn’t involve your “group.” No one’s helping you. But this is a choice about what kind of person you want to be. This is a choice about who you see in the mirror.</p>
<p>You can be a creator of some small good, or a spectator to our lesser angels. I hope the choice is easy.</p>
<p><em>Tim Kowalczyk is a Trinity senior. His column runs on alternate Wednesdays.</em></p>

